Package: BayesMendel
Version: 2.1-4
Date: 2017/07/28
Title: Determining Carrier Probabilities for Cancer Susceptibility
        Genes
Description: BayesMendel calculates the probability of carrying mutations of the cancer susceptibility genes (BRCA1 and BRCA2 for breast/ovarian cancer, MLH1/MSH2/MSH6 for colon/rectum/endometrium cancer, hypothetical PANC gene for pancreas cancer, and P16 for melanoma).  The calculation is based on an individual's family history of the cancer(s) in first- and second-degree relatives and, if available, on the results of genetic testing for the genes. Version as of 2.0-81 run peeling through c-code by calling peelingRC.
Author: Giovanni Parmigiani <gp@jimmy.harvard.edu>, Sining Chen, Wenyi Wang, Hormuzd Katki and Amanda Blackford. Adapted from C code written by Omar Aguilar and Giovanni Parmigiani, with contributions by Sining Chen, Daniel F. Gudbjartsson, Kathy Zhou, Edwin S. Iversen, Jr 
License: GPL (>= 3) | file LICENSE
Maintainer: Amanda Blackford <ablackf1@jhmi.edu>
